com.facebook.buck.java

Class DefaultJavaLibraryRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.AbstractCachingBuildRule
      • com.facebook.buck.rules.DoNotUseAbstractBuildable
        • com.facebook.buck.java.DefaultJavaLibraryRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasClasspathEntries, HasJavaSrcs, JavaAbiRule, JavaLibraryRule, AbiRule, Buildable, BuildRule, ExportDependencies, InitializableFromDisk<JavaLibraryRule.Data>, Comparable<BuildRule>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndroidLibraryRule, JavaTestRule

    public class DefaultJavaLibraryRule
extends DoNotUseAbstractBuildable
implements JavaLibraryRule, AbiRule, HasJavaSrcs, HasClasspathEntries, ExportDependencies, InitializableFromDisk<JavaLibraryRule.Data>
    Suppose this were a rule defined in src/com/facebook/feed/BUILD: 
     java_library(
   name = 'feed',
   srcs = [
     'FeedStoryRenderer.java',
   ],
   deps = [
     '//src/com/facebook/feed/model:model',
     '//third-party/java/guava:guava',
   ],
 )
    Then this would compile FeedStoryRenderer.java against Guava and the classes generated from the //src/com/facebook/feed/model:model rule.

      • createTotalAbiKey

        protected Sha1HashCode createTotalAbiKey(Sha1HashCode abiKey)
        Creates the total ABI key for this rule. If export_deps is true, the total key is computed by hashing the ABI keys of the dependencies together with the ABI key of this rule. If export_deps is false, the standalone ABI key for this rule is used as the total key.
        Parameters:
        abiKey - the standalone ABI key for this rule.
        Returns:
        total ABI key containing also the ABI keys of the dependencies.

      • appendToRuleKey

        public RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder)
                                throws IOException
        getRuleKey() and getRuleKeyWithoutDeps() uses this when constructing RuleKeys for this class. Every subclass that extends the rule state in a way that matters to idempotency must override appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) and append its state to the RuleKey.Builder returned by its superclass's appendToRuleKey(com.facebook.buck.rules.RuleKey.Builder) implementation. Example: 
         @Override
 protected RuleKey.Builder appendToRuleKey(RuleKey.Builder builder) {
   return super.appendToRuleKey(builder)
       .set("srcs", srcs),
       .set("resources", resources);
 }

      • getAbiKey

        public Sha1HashCode getAbiKey()
        Description copied from interface: JavaLibraryRule
        Returns a SHA-1 hash that represents the ABI for the Java files returned by JavaLibraryRule.getJavaSrcs(). If JavaLibraryRule.getJavaSrcs() returns an empty collection, then this will return a non-absent value. The only requirement on the hash is that equal hashes imply equal ABIs.

        Because the ABI is computed as part of the build process, this rule cannot be invoked until after this rule is built.

        Specified by:
        getAbiKey in interface JavaAbiRule
        Specified by:
        getAbiKey in interface JavaLibraryRule

      • getDeps

        public final ImmutableSortedSet<BuildRule> getDeps()
        Specified by:
        getDeps in interface BuildRule
        Returns:
        the set of rules that must be built before this rule. Normally, this matches the value of the deps argument for this build rule in the build file in which it was defined.

        However, there are special cases where other arguments pull in implicit dependencies (e.g., the keystore argument in android_binary). In these cases, the implicit dependencies are also included in the set returned by this method. The value of the original deps argument, as defined in the build file, must be accessed via a custom getter provided by the build rule.
